    IFPEXTRA Update selected Bulk Data records from NEWIFP1958 Main Index From tables output by the NEWIFP module modify entries depending on parameter xCompSpt. If xCompSpt is TRUE, converts LAM and SOUT of PCOMP and PCOMPG from Hollerith characters to intergers as well as convert negative spoint ids to positive. If xCompSpt is FALSE, it modifies below entries accordingly: 1.PCOMP, PCOMPG and DVPRELi entries are used to create the PCOMPT table. 2.CSEAM entries are modified and used to create additional GRID entries. 3.TEMPBC entries are removed and converted to SPC or DAREA and CELAS2 entries. 4.TABLRPC entries are converted to TABLED1 entries. 5.This module also checks the correctness of CNA and CNB of RBAR entries in GEOM4 datablock. Format: Input Data Blocks:IFPEXTRA Update selected Bulk Data records from NEWIFP IFPEXTRA EPT,EDOM,GEOM1,GEOM2,GEOM4,DYNAMIC,MPT,DIT,EDT,CASECC,MODLIST/ PCOMPT,GEOM1N,GEOM2N,GEOM4N,DYNAMICN,EDOMN,EPTN,MPTN,DITN,EDTnew,CASEnew/ xCompSpt/S,N,XPCOMPT/S,N,XGEOM1/S,N,XGEOM2/S,N,XGEOM4/S,N,XDYNAMIC/ S,N,XEDOM/S,N,XEPT/S,N,XMPT/S,N,XDIT/s,n,xEDT/s,n,xCASE/S,N,RESET/ S,N,NOGO/RDCHECK/SOLFLG/SEID/LOCMOD/SOL128/doH5DA $ EPT T able of Bulk Data entry images related to element properties. PCOMP/PCOMPG entries will be processed. EDOM T able of Bulk Data entries related to design sensitivity and optimization. DVPRELi entries will be processed. GEOM1 T able of Bulk Data entry images related to geometry. GRID entries will be processed. GEOM2 T able of Bulk Data entry images related to element connectivity and scalar points. CSEAM and CELAS2 entries will be processed. GEOM4 T able of Bulk Data entry images related to constraints, degree-of-freedom membership and rigid element connectivity. SPC and TEMPBC entries will be processed. DYNAMIC T ables of Bulk Data entry images related to dynamics. DAREA entries will be processed. MPT T able of Bulk Data entry images related to material properties. DIT T able of Bulk Data entry images related to table. EDT T able of Bulk Data entry images related to SETi and UDNAME. CASECC T able of Case control entry image. MODLIST List of BEGIN MODULE IDs.
